<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: CrackrJak</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-07-14 00:46:47</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Just got my 1st EBS for 400pp, I couldn't believe it was being auctioned so low and I was fortunate the seller was patient enough to let me run to the bank 4 zones away.<BR>
<BR>
As for dungeon fights, I've been in mistmoore and splitpaw with it and have yet to cause a train. But I do warn all I group with of its proc of ensnaring roots. a pull of 3 Tech Mas Gnolls hasn't killed me or my group members. Rangers, ALWAYS ask what the groups game plan is and invite a good druid in your group, as well as an enchanter! Make sure the <BR>
warriors you group with have an excellent Taunt. This should be common sense in ANY dungeon where SOW cannot be cast. <BR>
<BR>
Another trick, Have a Necromancer stand in back of the group near the most likely avenue of escape for your prey.<BR>
Have him/her fear the creature as it tries to run, it will<BR>
run back to your melee types, be killed and viola potential problem solved, by good planning. <BR>
<BR>
Keep this sword! At least until you can get a Ykesha. <BR>
Its a free spell and, despite its detractors comments, can be very handy when things need kiting. 90% of the area in the game is outdoors, and good dungeon plans prevent trains.<BR>
<BR>
</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
